text:

text:

Leeds 2-2 Chelsea, more energy sapping extra time at Wembley (criticism of the pitch to follow separately!). United would have to find enough in the tank to face Celtic in the European Cup, never mind the #FACup replay & finish the league prog! #lufc

author: üíõü§çüíôLUSC GriffinüèÜüèÜüèÜ
text:
2/7 cont...
#OnThisDay 1970 #FACup Final.
United's marathon season drawing close to a frustratingly sad end. Leeds were playing the 14th game in 43 days - Including fixtures on consecutive days. The demand was too great. The league title conceded to go for the cups. #lufc

author: PickGuru
text:
The FA Cup returns tomorrow üèÜ

For yet another season, one of the "big six" will be in the final.

text:

The Road to Wembley
#FACup semi final - 23rd April

author: The Road to Wembley (FA Cup Finals 1923 - 2000)
text:
Remembering the late Sir Stanley Rous who was born OTD in 1895.

Rous, a regular figure at the #FACup final, often seen in the Royal Box, was also a steward at the very first Wembley FA cup final in 1923 & also refereed the 1934 final.
